flowchart LR

  subgraph INTENT["1. Path objective"]
    G1["Turn a boundary-valid request into truthful ingress decision"]
    G2["Make the ingress ownership boundary decide the event's disposition explicitly"]
    G3["Stop this path at ingress truth rather than letting it collapse into bus publication"]
  end

  subgraph ENTRY["2. Entry basis"]
    E1["The entry is not raw engine data in general"]
    E2["It is a request that has already crossed the active front door under the correct route and auth contract"]
    E3["The request carries traffic that is actually allowed to behave as traffic"]
    E4["Only behavioural_streams are canonical business traffic and must conform to the canonical event-envelope contract"]
    E5["Current traffic policy is the dual-stream posture: s2_event_stream_baseline_6B and s3_event_stream_with_fraud_6B"]
    E6["The active request contract is API Gateway base URL + POST /ingest/push + X-IG-Api-Key"]
  end

  subgraph SPINE["5. Broad route logic"]
    R1["Boundary-accepted request"]
    R2["IG handler applies ingress contract"]
    R3["Canonical dedupe and admission basis is computed"]
    R4["Authoritative idempotency and admission state is written"]
    R5["Truthful disposition is returned and made available for later evidence closure"]
  end

  subgraph CARRIES["4. What the path carries"]
    C1["Run identity: platform_run_id"]
    C2["Event identity: event_class + event_id"]
    C3["Payload identity: payload hash"]
    C4["Dedupe identity: canonical dedupe_key"]
    C5["Retention and idempotency timing: TTL field"]
    C6["Disposition metadata: state, admitted timestamp, and reason codes when present"]
    C7["The selected IG patch computes deterministic SHA-256 dedupe_key from (platform_run_id, event_class, event_id)"]
    C8["The Lambda writes a DynamoDB item keyed by that dedupe basis and stores minimal admission metadata"]
    C9["The path fail-closes with 503 when the idempotency backend is unavailable"]
  end

  subgraph LOGIC["6. Logical design reading"]
    L1["The platform treats ingress truth as its own boundary-owned truth, not just prelude to Kafka"]
    L2["The system is not saying: an event counts as handled once something downstream eventually sees it"]
    L3["It is saying: the ingress plane itself owns deterministic dedupe and disposition judgment"]
    L4["That matches the broader semantic law that truth ownership boundaries must be preserved"]
    L5["It also matches the ingress-plane requirement that there be one authoritative dedupe boundary"]
  end

  subgraph SEATING["7. Concrete seating in the current wired system"]
    S1["Default ingress posture is API Gateway + Lambda + DynamoDB idempotency store"]
    S2["The live edge contract is pinned by active ingress URL, ingest route, authentication mode, and secret-backed API key contract"]
    S3["The active IG edge runtime is API Gateway -> Lambda -> DynamoDB"]
    S4["Remediation work made the Lambda path persist idempotency and admission records into DynamoDB"]
    S5["That gave the lane non-zero, run-scoped admission truth"]
  end

  subgraph RATIONALE["8. Why the design looks like this"]
    Y1["Before the patch, /ingest/push could return 202 without persisting any run-scoped admission or idempotency record"]
    Y2["That was rejected as structurally wrong because the ingress plane then had no durable proof of its own decision"]
    Y3["Direct DynamoDB seed writes were rejected because they bypass the ingress boundary and would not prove runtime semantics"]
    Y4["Treating the issue as non-blocking was rejected because it would violate the fail-closed gate contract"]
    Y5["So the selected fix was boundary correction: put truthful admission persistence inside the IG Lambda path itself"]
  end

  subgraph CONTRACT["9. What larger contracts are shaping this path"]
    X1["The engine interface shapes what may even appear at ingress"]
    X2["Only behavioural_streams are canonical traffic"]
    X3["Canonical traffic must conform to the event-envelope contract"]
    X4["Non-traffic surfaces must not be treated as business traffic"]
    X5["Platform authority shapes how ingress is allowed to exist"]
    X6["Managed-first ingress posture"]
    X7["Explicit dedupe identity and payload-hash anomaly law"]
    X8["Explicit truth boundaries and no silent defaults or toy substitutes in pinned lanes"]
    X9["So this path is constrained both by what may enter and by how ingress truth is allowed to be owned"]
  end

  subgraph TRADEOFFS["10. Trade-offs and constraints"]
    T1["This path deliberately accepts some hot-path ceremony in exchange for truthfulness"]
    T2["Durable dedupe and admission ledger adds write pressure and cost to the ingress hot path"]
    T3["The idempotency table later became a dominant cost surface when full receipt bodies were stored inline"]
    T4["The platform did not solve that by abandoning the ledger boundary"]
    T5["It kept the proven compact hot-table posture and compacted the stored receipt shape to the minimum fields needed for run attribution and lookup"]
    T6["The ownership boundary stayed the same while the concrete implementation was tightened"]
  end

  subgraph NECESSITY["11. Necessity test"]
    N1["If this path is removed, the ingress story becomes immediately weaker"]
    N2["The platform might still have a front door and might still publish some things later"]
    N3["But it would lose clean answers to: first-seen or duplicate, admitted or quarantined, what run the decision belonged to, and whether the ingress plane itself was behaving truthfully"]
    N4["It would also become unclear whether downstream starvation is a publication issue or whether the event was never actually admitted"]
    N5["Without this path, downstream components would be forced to infer ingress truth after the fact"]
    N6["That would blur ownership and directly weaken A"]
  end

  subgraph CLOSURE["3. Owned outcome and 12. What this path proves for A"]
    O1["admitted"]
    O2["duplicate-safe"]
    O3["rejected invalid"]
    O4["quarantined"]
    O5["explicitly marked ambiguous or retry-governed"]
    O6["Owned outcome: durable, truthful ingress disposition for this event under this run scope"]
    O7["This path stops at ingress truth; the bus handoff itself belongs to the next path"]
    A1["Purpose claim:<br/>ingress does not merely pass traffic through; it owns deterministic admission and disposition decision"]
    A2["Intentionality claim:<br/>the dedupe boundary and disposition logic are deliberate and explicit, not accidental consequences of downstream publish"]
    A3["Materialization claim:<br/>the path is concretely seated in the current API Gateway -> Lambda -> DynamoDB ingress posture with DynamoDB-backed idempotency and admission state"]
    A4["Contract claim:<br/>only the right traffic types are eligible, and ingress truth remains ingress truth"]
    A5["Quantified closure claim:<br/>the ingest-commit gate later requires admit and quarantine summaries plus dedupe and anomaly checks, so this path has named evidence closure downstream in the runbook"]
    A6["A-level meaning:<br/>ingress truth becomes explicit before event-bus truth begins"]
  end

